      • federateTime

        protected double federateTime
        the time of this federate

      • federateLookahead

        protected double federateLookahead
        The minimum amount of time ahead of federate time this federate can schedule a future event. The federate cannot publish events sooner than currentTime + lookahead

      • isRegulating

        protected boolean isRegulating
        Regulating means that this federate issues timestamped events--thus causing other federates to not advance their clocks because we may issue events that they must process

      • isConstrained

        protected boolean isConstrained
        Constrained means that this federate consumes timestamped events; thus it cannot advance it's clock time without considering the time state of federates that issue time stamped events

      • isAdvancing

        protected boolean isAdvancing
        The federate is in "time-advancing" state, that is it is receiving time-stamped messages.
